spans.text: the beams of the morning sun
the ragged fragments of the shrinking rock
thick as the hail in the howling storm , driven down the mountain's side , the son of the tempest ; the chariot , and the horse
the river be swelled with the smoking streams of life
the praises of the gods : let the image be filled with the bodies of the dead , for the foe is swept away like purple bloom of the grape , no more to be seen
the bodies of the dead , for the foe is swept away like purple bloom of the grape , no more to be seen
the silver javelin and the pointed shield
who shake the silver javelin and the pointed shield
to council at the tent of Cerdick
the coppice heath , the chiefs of the war
Graceful as the flower that overlooks the silver stream , the mighty Cerdick
the hills like the stones of hail
the god of battle fans the air , the red sword waves in their banner
their eyes be feasted with the chaplets of victory
the lightning on his shield ! his eyes are two stars , his arm
the chaplet hangs on his helm
that Kenrick shall sit on my throne
the cries of the burning so
